Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_metric(25.10)                                      report_metric(25.10)

Name
       report_metric  -  Allows  the  user to generate reports in various file
       formats

Syntax
       report_metric

       [-help]

       <pattern>

       -format {html json excel text vivid}

       [-id <metricID>]

       [-names <listOfNames>]

       [-out_file <fileName>]

       Allows the user to generate reports in various file formats.

Parameters
       -format {html json excel text vivid}
              Specifies the output type.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each report_metric parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man report_metric

       -id <metricID>
              Specifies the ID of metrics to report.

              Supports  multiple  metric  IDs  for excel and html formats. The
              first ID specified will be considered the "gold" value for  com-
              parison with other IDs.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -names <listOfNames>
              Specifies the list of names.

              Data_type: string, optional

              Note: Wildcards are supported.

       <pattern>
              Specifies the pattern to match.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -out_file<fileName >
              Specifies the name of the target file.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following  example writes the YAML structure in the text format in
       small.text, reads the YAML file, and generates the report in  the  text
       format.

       > write_metric_config -format text small.text ;

       > read_metric_config -format text small.yaml

       > report_metric  -format text

Related Information
              * read_metric_config

              * write_metric_config

